# I'm trying to tell you 
something bout my life #

3
00:00:10,753 --> 00:00:15,995
# Maybe give me insight 
between black and white #

4
00:00:15,995 --> 00:00:20,680
# And the best thing 
you've ever done for me #

5
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:24,741
# Is to help me take 
my life less seriously #

6
00:00:24,741 --> 00:00:29,310
# It's only life after all #

7
00:00:30,818 --> 00:00:35,627
# Now darkness has 
a hunger that's insatiable #

8
00:00:35,627 --> 00:00:40,442
# And lightness has 
a call that's hard to hear #

9
00:00:40,442 --> 00:00:45,377
# I wrap my fear around 
me like a blanket #

10
00:00:45,377 --> 00:00:49,120
# I sailed my ship of 
safety till I sank it #

11
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:52,162
# I'm crawling on your shores #

12
00:01:31,954 --> 00:01:33,210
What's up?

13
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:35,027
You know Lindesy Dunlay?

14
00:01:35,027 --> 00:01:36,007
No.

15
00:01:36,007 --> 00:01:38,907
Court-appointed child psychologist,
I went to high school with her.

16
00:01:38,907 --> 00:01:40,275
Oh, yeah? What she want with us?

17
00:01:40,275 --> 00:01:43,391
Case of hers. Sean Morgan was
arrested for a strong-arm.

18
00:01:43,391 --> 00:01:45,491
Judge sent him to Lindsey for evaluation.

19
00:01:45,491 --> 00:01:46,036
And?

20
00:01:46,036 --> 00:01:49,293
When he was three, Sean 
witnessed his mother's murder.

21
00:01:49,293 --> 00:01:50,644
The case was never solved. / Lil!

22
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:52,215
Hey, Lindsey. / Hey.

23
00:01:52,215 --> 00:01:53,232
It's my partner Scotty Valens.

24
00:01:53,232 --> 00:01:54,798
How you doing? / Good.

25
00:01:54,798 --> 00:01:57,351
So, uh, what was she like in high school?

26
00:01:57,351 --> 00:01:58,903
She'll never tell, right?

27
00:01:58,903 --> 00:02:02,016
Let's just say Lilly and I 
never made the year book.

28
00:02:02,648 --> 00:02:04,789
The holy terror is over there.

29
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,119
What's his deal?

30
00:02:06,119 --> 00:02:08,840
17-year-old thug in the making.

31
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:11,455
Sean came up in foster care?

32
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,983
I'm hoping the judge goes easy,

33
00:02:14,983 --> 00:02:17,318
'cause in another year 
he gets the big time.

34
00:02:17,318 --> 00:02:18,490
What was the robbery?

35
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:20,471
Purse snatching off an LOL.

36
00:02:20,471 --> 00:02:22,892
Done two others just like it.

37
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:24,725
He's next to hopeless.

38
00:02:24,725 --> 00:02:28,015
But it seems like he has some real 
memories of his mom getting killed.

39
00:02:28,015 --> 00:02:29,698
That's why I called you.

40
00:02:29,698 --> 00:02:31,302
He never told anyone about it?

41
00:02:31,302 --> 00:02:33,135
No one that believed him.

42
00:02:37,405 --> 00:02:40,970
Sean, this is Detective Rush 
who I told you about.

43
00:02:41,401 --> 00:02:43,509
My partner Detective Valens.

44
00:02:43,509 --> 00:02:45,126
Partners, huh?

45
00:02:45,485 --> 00:02:47,584
You hit that yet?

46
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:50,215
I know I just misunderstood you, Sean.

47
00:02:50,215 --> 00:02:51,829
I'm about to turn 18.

48
00:02:51,829 --> 00:02:54,705
If he don't man-up real soon, 
maybe you and I could hook it up.

49
00:02:54,705 --> 00:02:56,595
Yeah, yeah, I'll think about it.

50
00:02:56,595 --> 00:03:00,136
Sean, stop wasting their time 
and tell them about your mom.

51
00:03:00,669 --> 00:03:03,801
Lindesy said you had some specific 
memories about her being killed?

52
00:03:03,801 --> 00:03:04,988
I forget 'em.

53
00:03:04,988 --> 00:03:07,510
So you like stealing from old 
ladies, huh? That's impressive.

54
00:03:07,510 --> 00:03:08,901
What do you know about it, smalls?

55
00:03:08,901 --> 00:03:13,478
I know I got better things to do that 
monkey with a kid trying to get attention.

56
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,048
Let's bounce.

57
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,835
I'm sorry, I thought this kid was different.

58
00:03:26,576 --> 00:03:27,951
What?

59
00:03:28,237 --> 00:03:29,977
You get ignored all the time, right?

60
00:03:29,977 --> 00:03:33,553
Treated like what you say
either ain't true or worth crap.

61
00:03:33,553 --> 00:03:34,976
Yeah, that's about it.

62
00:03:34,976 --> 00:03:37,515
And here come two people who want 
to listen to what you have to say

63
00:03:37,515 --> 00:03:39,136
and you're letting us walk away?

64
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:42,906
You want your mom's case 
looked at, we're your chance.

65
00:03:43,995 --> 00:03:46,627
Why should I believe you?

66
00:03:46,627 --> 00:03:48,629
Look at me.

67
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,597
Am I lying?

68
00:03:58,705 --> 00:04:01,534
Red and yellow balloons.

69
00:04:03,258 --> 00:04:06,996
A train and the name "Bobby".

70
00:04:07,493 --> 00:04:11,086
That's what I remember 
about her being murdered.

