521
00:24:20,512 --> 00:24:21,912
Assaults, theft.

522
00:24:21,912 --> 00:24:24,776
But so far, the juvenile 
courts have bailed him out.

523
00:24:24,776 --> 00:24:26,570
Mr. and Mrs. Gordon,

524
00:24:26,570 --> 00:24:29,594
ever known someone 
named Linda Frandsen?

525
00:24:29,594 --> 00:24:31,165
She the one who took our boy?

526
00:24:31,165 --> 00:24:34,543
Frandsen? Wasn't that what's 
his name ex-wife, the landscaper?

527
00:24:34,543 --> 00:24:35,762
Hector?

528
00:24:35,762 --> 00:24:37,151
Victor.

529
00:24:37,151 --> 00:24:38,213
Lake?

530
00:24:38,213 --> 00:24:39,594
Yeah.

531
00:24:41,043 --> 00:24:43,767
Linda came by with him once.

532
00:24:52,548 --> 00:24:54,312
What a sweetie!

533
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,834
How old is he?

534
00:24:55,834 --> 00:24:57,624
Ten months.

535
00:24:58,902 --> 00:24:59,912
What's his name?

536
00:24:59,912 --> 00:25:01,046
Bobby.

537
00:25:01,046 --> 00:25:02,559
Bobby!

538
00:25:03,181 --> 00:25:05,647
You're just a little miracle, 
aren't you, Bobby?

539
00:25:05,647 --> 00:25:09,300
That's what I tell myself as I'm 
combing the Cheerios out of my hair.

540
00:25:10,328 --> 00:25:12,236
Can I tell you a secret? / Sure.

541
00:25:12,236 --> 00:25:13,617
I'm expecting.

542
00:25:13,617 --> 00:25:15,537
That's wonderful.

543
00:25:15,537 --> 00:25:17,815
I think it's a boy.

544
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:25,575
She seemed lovely.

545
00:25:26,391 --> 00:25:27,800
They came off decent enough.

546
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,543
Yeah, we know Vic.

547
00:25:29,543 --> 00:25:31,822
When can we see Bobby?

548
00:25:32,584 --> 00:25:34,624
He goes by "Sean" now.

549
00:25:34,624 --> 00:25:36,389
And he doesn't know about you yet,

550
00:25:36,389 --> 00:25:40,480
but Child Services will be 
in touch to facilitate things.

551
00:25:41,493 --> 00:25:46,667
Will you tell him that we miss 
him and we want to see him.

552
00:25:49,204 --> 00:25:50,425
Why?

553
00:25:51,501 --> 00:25:52,397
Why what?

554
00:25:52,397 --> 00:25:55,537
You came here because you 
want to solve her murder?

555
00:25:55,537 --> 00:25:59,101
Why? To hell with her.

556
00:26:12,822 --> 00:26:13,752
How'd it go?

557
00:26:13,752 --> 00:26:15,219
He's getting another chance.

558
00:26:15,219 --> 00:26:19,614
But if he so much as jaywalks during 
probation, Judge Haze will look him up.

559
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:23,982
So, you want to do girl's night soon?

560
00:26:24,644 --> 00:26:25,186
Yeah.

561
00:26:25,186 --> 00:26:29,639
Of course, if you'd rather go 
fly a kite, I'd understand.

562
00:26:31,076 --> 00:26:33,587
Who you been talking to?

563
00:26:40,405 --> 00:26:43,899
Oh, man, my shadow again.

564
00:26:43,899 --> 00:26:45,764
You caught a break today, huh?

565
00:26:45,764 --> 00:26:46,962
I don't know.

566
00:26:46,962 --> 00:26:48,357
You did, Sean.

567
00:26:48,670 --> 00:26:50,575
Don't screw it up.

568
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:53,931
Thank you for your advice.

569
00:26:56,105 --> 00:26:59,056
Her name was Linda Fransen.

570
00:27:00,615 --> 00:27:02,445
I told you I could give a heave-ho.

571
00:27:02,445 --> 00:27:05,084
She kidnapped you when you were two.

572
00:27:06,137 --> 00:27:08,571
Man, you keep trying to shock 
me and you keep missing.

573
00:27:08,571 --> 00:27:11,294
I'm just giving you the straight story.

574
00:27:12,648 --> 00:27:14,276
Here's the rest :

575
00:27:16,069 --> 00:27:17,781
we found your parents.

576
00:27:17,781 --> 00:27:19,315
What?

577
00:27:19,791 --> 00:27:21,202
Yeah.

578
00:27:21,202 --> 00:27:23,458
Mom and Dad?

579
00:27:23,937 --> 00:27:26,145
I got a bunch of brothers and sisters, too?

580
00:27:26,145 --> 00:27:27,897
Two brothers.

581
00:27:29,214 --> 00:27:30,487
You know what?

582
00:27:30,487 --> 00:27:32,634
You can have 'em.

583
00:27:32,634 --> 00:27:35,295
They don't want me, they want you.

584
00:27:35,295 --> 00:27:37,299
You talk to 'em?

585
00:27:38,802 --> 00:27:40,149
They want to meet you.

586
00:27:40,149 --> 00:27:41,434
I bet.

587
00:27:41,434 --> 00:27:44,310
They got to be thrilled their 
kid's a juvie delinquent.

588
00:27:44,310 --> 00:27:46,463
Sean, you got a family waiting for you.

589
00:27:46,463 --> 00:27:48,636
I don't want a family.

590
00:27:49,064 --> 00:27:51,007
I would have settled to have 
one parent looking out for me.

591
00:27:51,007 --> 00:27:53,340
Here you got two and you're snubbing it?

592
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:56,834
I didn't realize you were such a hothead.

593
00:27:57,609 --> 00:28:01,804
Sean, you can be the kind of 
kid they want, or be a thug.

594
00:28:01,804 --> 00:28:03,661
It's up to you.

595
00:28:06,643 --> 00:28:08,921
Snatching babies, huh, Vic?

596
00:28:08,921 --> 00:28:09,999
What?

597
00:28:09,999 --> 00:28:12,152
Thought you'd work the 
old razzle-dazzle on us,

598
00:28:12,152 --> 00:28:14,668
send us to Dr. Silver
and the trail would end there.

599
00:28:14,668 --> 00:28:15,942
But it didn't.

600
00:28:15,942 --> 00:28:18,281
I'm sorry. You fellows are losing me.

601
00:28:18,281 --> 00:28:21,084
It led to your old employers, the Gordons.

602
00:28:21,084 --> 00:28:24,371
Yeah, where you and Linda stole a baby.

603
00:28:24,371 --> 00:28:25,421
Come on.

604
00:28:25,421 --> 00:28:27,935
And afterwards, we're thinking 
Linda must have ditched you.

605
00:28:27,935 --> 00:28:30,274
Yeah, that's why you looked 
her up, to wipe her out.

606
00:28:30,274 --> 00:28:31,357
I want a lawyer.

607
00:28:31,357 --> 00:28:33,016
We'll get you a judge and jury, too.

608
00:28:33,016 --> 00:28:34,652
You do that, 'cause I didn't kill her.

609
00:28:34,652 --> 00:28:37,417
Say we're in the jury box 
and we're eyeballing Vic here.

610
00:28:37,417 --> 00:28:38,564
We know he's a kidnapper.

611
00:28:38,564 --> 00:28:39,659
I didn't do that.

612
00:28:39,659 --> 00:28:41,497
You ain't going to beat that one, Vic.

613
00:28:41,497 --> 00:28:43,021
That'd be a one-in-a-million shot.

614
00:28:43,021 --> 00:28:44,919
Think about how whupped
he was by this Linda,

615
00:28:44,919 --> 00:28:46,929
so much he swiped a baby for her.

616
00:28:46,929 --> 00:28:49,208
Did a federal crime for his lady

617
00:28:49,208 --> 00:28:51,114
and she gives you the high hat?

618
00:28:51,114 --> 00:28:52,647
I see motive, real clear.

619
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:53,270
Oh, yeah.

620
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:55,402
Who do you think the jury's 
going to put the murder on?

621
00:28:55,402 --> 00:28:56,800
I did not do murder.

622
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,254
Okay. Good luck with that.

623
00:28:58,254 --> 00:29:00,068
I didn't.

624
00:29:00,068 --> 00:29:03,306
I only ripped off the kid.

625
00:29:06,004 --> 00:29:10,831
After Linda lost that other yo-yo's 
baby, she come back to me.

626
00:29:11,333 --> 00:29:13,788
I wanted her to stay.

627
00:29:14,917 --> 00:29:17,797
I said I'd do anything.

628
00:29:18,051 --> 00:29:20,066
What'd she say?

629
00:29:20,668 --> 00:29:21,894
"Prove it."

630
00:29:42,487 --> 00:29:43,265
Anyone see you?

631
00:29:43,265 --> 00:29:44,762
I don't know.

632
00:29:44,762 --> 00:29:47,151
Calm down. Calm... Look at me.

633
00:29:47,151 --> 00:29:48,528
Hand him over.

634
00:29:48,528 --> 00:29:50,253
Give me my boy.

635
00:29:52,226 --> 00:29:53,083
Scoot over, I'll drive.

636
00:29:53,083 --> 00:29:54,498
No, darling, you got to get back.

637
00:29:54,498 --> 00:29:55,516
Finish your work.

638
00:29:55,516 --> 00:29:57,400
I can't go back. I'm nervous.

639
00:29:57,400 --> 00:30:00,207
Horse, you're such my baby, too.

640
00:30:00,207 --> 00:30:03,350
You go on. You be strong for me, okay?

641
00:30:03,350 --> 00:30:05,924
In a few hours, you'll be 
seeing us at the motel.

642
00:30:05,924 --> 00:30:07,396
Go on.

643
00:30:08,219 --> 00:30:10,070
Go on.

644
00:30:12,819 --> 00:30:15,458
I got back to the motel that 
night, she'd cleared out.

645
00:30:15,458 --> 00:30:16,847
Just like that?

646
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:18,932
She left a note.

647
00:30:19,372 --> 00:30:21,831
Said she's going to Philly 
to find us new haunts.

648
00:30:21,831 --> 00:30:23,442
That she'd send for me.

649
00:30:23,442 --> 00:30:26,710
Meanwhile, I'm supposed to keep 
clocking in over at the Gordon's.

650
00:30:26,710 --> 00:30:29,130
Never got the call, huh?

651
00:30:30,125 --> 00:30:32,657
Weeks turned into years.

652
00:30:32,657 --> 00:30:35,450
Who else knew she came to Philadelphia?

653
00:30:36,716 --> 00:30:39,254
A few years later, I told this guy

654
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:40,833
that'd come around asking 
questions about her.

655
00:30:40,833 --> 00:30:41,797
What guy?

656
00:30:41,797 --> 00:30:43,670
A private investigator.

657
00:30:43,670 --> 00:30:46,148
P.I. say what he wanted with Linda?

658
00:30:46,148 --> 00:30:48,155
No, I didn't push it.

659
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:51,711
I was pretty torqued off by then.

660
00:30:51,711 --> 00:30:55,415
I told him, "Hey, she's somewhere in Philly."

661
00:30:57,354 --> 00:30:59,561
Vic copped to the kidnapping,
not the murder.

662
00:30:59,561 --> 00:31:00,641
You believe him?

663
00:31:00,641 --> 00:31:02,247
Linda humiliate him pretty good.

664
00:31:02,247 --> 00:31:03,675
Made a fool of Ned, too.

665
00:31:03,675 --> 00:31:05,632
Seems like that was kind of the 
way she walked through life.

666
00:31:05,632 --> 00:31:07,509
Got a trail of guys behind her she duped.

667
00:31:07,509 --> 00:31:09,867
Eventually, one of 'em didn't sit still for it.

668
00:31:09,867 --> 00:31:13,016
The P.I. who approached Vic was a 
weasel by the name of Isiah Bagley.

669
00:31:13,016 --> 00:31:14,118
Did he say who worked for?

670
00:31:14,118 --> 00:31:17,282
You'r gonna love this. Dr. Kyle Silver.

671
00:31:18,922 --> 00:31:19,211
Homicide.

672
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:21,322
Why's a doctor hire a P.I.?

673
00:31:21,322 --> 00:31:23,041
Thought he was glad she split.

674
00:31:23,041 --> 00:31:24,969
Bagley said he wanted 
her found at any cost.

675
00:31:24,969 --> 00:31:26,453
Okay, thanks.

676
00:31:27,698 --> 00:31:29,601
That was your friend Lindsey.

677
00:31:30,097 --> 00:31:33,036
Sean just got picked up for stealing a car.

678
00:31:52,465 --> 00:31:55,245
My lawyer says I could get two years.

679
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:57,208
I heard.

680
00:31:58,163 --> 00:32:00,055
So I'm supposed to sit 
in this joint for two years?

681
00:32:00,055 --> 00:32:02,397
You stole a car and you were drunk.

682
00:32:02,397 --> 00:32:03,110
Three beers.

683
00:32:03,110 --> 00:32:04,580
Drunk driving can lead to homicide

684
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:07,225
and homicide leads to jail 
for the rest of your life.

685
00:32:07,225 --> 00:32:08,697
So I get it.

686
00:32:08,697 --> 00:32:11,459
You're as full of it as 
everyone else. / Sean...

687
00:32:11,459 --> 00:32:14,296
what is it that you want?

688
00:32:15,299 --> 00:32:17,794
Right now, to get up out of here.

689
00:32:19,237 --> 00:32:21,211
Say you're out...

690
00:32:21,910 --> 00:32:23,819
the foster homes, too.

691
00:32:23,819 --> 00:32:25,464
Then what?

692
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:27,559
I'm on the run and I'm not looking back.

693
00:32:27,559 --> 00:32:29,486
You taking anyone with you?

694
00:32:29,975 --> 00:32:30,980
A girl?

695
00:32:30,980 --> 00:32:32,369
Nah.

696
00:32:32,369 --> 00:32:34,468
I'm going to meet my woman.

697
00:32:34,682 --> 00:32:36,756
Someone who doesn't know you.

698
00:32:36,756 --> 00:32:38,123
Make a fresh start.

699
00:32:38,123 --> 00:32:39,538
Yeah.

700
00:32:39,783 --> 00:32:44,116
And me and her gonna
settle down, kick back

701
00:32:44,116 --> 00:32:46,621
and make a lot of love.

702
00:32:47,837 --> 00:32:49,473
Be careful.

703
00:32:49,473 --> 00:32:51,953
Nah, no jimmies for me.

704
00:32:51,953 --> 00:32:53,381
I want kids.

705
00:32:53,381 --> 00:32:55,671
I'm gonna have 13 of them.

706
00:32:55,671 --> 00:32:57,816
What are you gonna do for work?

707
00:32:58,114 --> 00:33:00,352
Whatever. I don't know.

708
00:33:00,352 --> 00:33:03,209
13 mouths do feed and you don't know?

709
00:33:04,377 --> 00:33:06,080
So not 13.

710
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,060
Maybe just one.

711
00:33:08,937 --> 00:33:10,897
Make it a girl.

712
00:33:12,111 --> 00:33:14,478
So what happens when your little girl

713
00:33:14,478 --> 00:33:16,860
comes home with a purple foot?

714
00:33:16,860 --> 00:33:18,260
Why would she get a purple foot?

715
00:33:18,260 --> 00:33:20,996
Because it's winter time 
and you got no job,

716
00:33:20,996 --> 00:33:22,568
your wife has new guy

717
00:33:22,568 --> 00:33:24,108
and  your daughter's 
got holes in her shoses.

718
00:33:24,108 --> 00:33:25,548
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- No, answer me,

719
00:33:25,548 --> 00:33:27,915
what are you gonna do?

720
00:33:28,355 --> 00:33:29,985
What are you gonna do?

721
00:33:29,985 --> 00:33:32,305
So you're saying I got no right 
to want anything in this life?

722
00:33:32,305 --> 00:33:35,581
No, no, no, you can have it all.

723
00:33:35,856 --> 00:33:37,498
But you're gonna need help.

724
00:33:37,498 --> 00:33:39,186
How would you know what I need?

725
00:33:39,186 --> 00:33:42,716
Because I wanted everything, too.

726
00:33:43,332 --> 00:33:50,001
But I was too damned proud to 
ask for help for way too long.

727
00:33:54,165 --> 00:33:56,325
Good luck, okay.

728
00:34:00,315 --> 00:34:03,533
I did wanna meet my family.

729
00:34:14,658 --> 00:34:15,980
Silver ever call back?

730
00:34:15,980 --> 00:34:17,483
He's here.

731
00:34:17,728 --> 00:34:19,548
Let's do it.

732
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:22,063
Detective.

733
00:34:24,912 --> 00:34:26,987
Mr. and Mrs. Gordon...

734
00:34:26,987 --> 00:34:28,530
what are you doing here?

735
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:30,159
We were told Bobby stole a car.

736
00:34:30,159 --> 00:34:33,802
Jeff, use his other name. Use Sean.

737
00:34:34,251 --> 00:34:35,467
How serious is this?

738
00:34:35,467 --> 00:34:36,466
Serious.

739
00:34:36,466 --> 00:34:39,216
He violated his probation, 
so he's in custody.

740
00:34:39,216 --> 00:34:41,211
Tomorrow morning he 
goes before a judge.

741
00:34:41,211 --> 00:34:42,881
Oh, God.

742
00:34:42,881 --> 00:34:44,402
Maybe we go back to the hotel,

743
00:34:44,402 --> 00:34:46,088
take the boys home.

744
00:34:46,088 --> 00:34:49,999
It might not be the best way 
for the boys to meet Sean.

745
00:34:50,215 --> 00:34:51,012
I see.

746
00:34:51,012 --> 00:34:53,958
We'll just wait till this 
whole thing blows over.

747
00:34:54,969 --> 00:34:58,342
Mr. and Mrs. Gordon, 
this isn't blowing over.

748
00:34:58,342 --> 00:35:01,611
Sean will probably go to jail
for the next two years.

749
00:35:02,099 --> 00:35:05,205
What if we showed up at the hearing,
would the judge show leniency?

750
00:35:05,205 --> 00:35:07,079
You can't count on that.

751
00:35:07,818 --> 00:35:11,872
For what it's worth, I know it'd be 
good for Sean to see you tomorrow.

752
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:15,735
Excuse us.

753
00:35:25,610 --> 00:35:27,311
Doctor...

754
00:35:28,391 --> 00:35:30,801
you said your wife almost divorced you,

755
00:35:30,801 --> 00:35:35,582
but the D.C. Superior Court says 
you initiated proceedings.

756
00:35:35,582 --> 00:35:37,496
I was the one who filed. Big deal

757
00:35:37,496 --> 00:35:40,678
It's not that you filed, Doc,
it's when you filed.

758
00:35:40,678 --> 00:35:43,325
September '89, a month 
before Linda was murdered.

759
00:35:43,325 --> 00:35:44,128
Please.

760
00:35:44,128 --> 00:35:45,705
And we know how bad you wanted Linda.

761
00:35:45,705 --> 00:35:46,779
I admitted that.

762
00:35:46,779 --> 00:35:48,721
Here's what I think, Doc.

763
00:35:48,721 --> 00:35:51,100
You already had the wife 
and kids, the experience,

764
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:53,375
so this time you wanted a little hottie

765
00:35:53,375 --> 00:35:56,521
to go off with, have a romp all over Europe.

766
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:58,566
Yeah, Linda was your girl...

767
00:35:58,566 --> 00:36:00,040
so sexy it was silly.

768
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:02,682
But when you tracked her down,
you find a baby, too.

769
00:36:02,682 --> 00:36:03,307
Bummer.

770
00:36:03,307 --> 00:36:05,638
And now she don't want you 
anymore, she only wants the kid.

771
00:36:05,638 --> 00:36:08,362
So you damn near take her head off.

772
00:36:11,025 --> 00:36:12,273
Tough to look at, huh?

773
00:36:12,273 --> 00:36:13,614
Yeah.

774
00:36:13,614 --> 00:36:15,188
'Cause she was a decent girl.

775
00:36:15,188 --> 00:36:18,211
Silver, we know you hired P.I. to find Linda.

776
00:36:18,211 --> 00:36:22,509
You had Isiah Bagley on the case 
for six months, so don't tell us

777
00:36:23,024 --> 00:36:25,885
you never went to see her again.

778
00:36:27,955 --> 00:36:29,509
Okay, I visited Linda.

779
00:36:29,509 --> 00:36:33,598
On October 11, 1989, that night?

780
00:36:36,376 --> 00:36:39,247
It was somewhat like you said.

781
00:36:40,242 --> 00:36:43,713
I went there to take Linda away, 
but she didn't want to go.

782
00:36:44,221 --> 00:36:46,570
But I took it in stride.

783
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:49,097
You just left.

